---
title: Pan-Seared Sole with Salsa Verde, Fingerling Potatoes, and Lemony Green Beans
description: Every cuisine has its own version of a green sauce. In Argentina, it’s chimichurri; in France, it’s sauce verte; and  in Spain and Italy, salsa verde. Our chefs put their own spin on the Italian version by incorporating green olives and parsley. It adds a major pop of flavor to this light yet satisfying dinner.
